# Parallel Delegation In Chat

When handling user requests in this project chat:

- Auto-delegate large or multi-part tasks to subagents in parallel (up to 4).
- If the user asks to force splitting (e.g. "split across 3 agents"), obey exactly up to 4.
- Launch parallel subagents in a single tool call batch when possible.
- For execution-heavy requests, delegate implementation work (not only analysis).
- Give each subagent a distinct, non-overlapping objective and return a merged final result.
- Prefer 2-4 agents only for broad, complex, or high-token tasks; keep narrow tasks single-agent.
- For forced delegation, do not ask for confirmation unless constraints are unclear.

## Trigger Heuristics

Treat a task as "large" if one or more apply:

- User asks for end-to-end implementation touching multiple files/systems.
- Prompt contains many requirements, steps, or broad exploration + implementation.
- The request would benefit from independent streams (explore, implement, test, summarize).

## Execution-First Delegation

If the user intent is implementation, delegate executable workstreams by default:

- stream A: feature implementation
- stream B: tests/verification scaffolding
- stream C: docs/config wiring
- stream D: integration and final conflict-free assembly

## Fallback

If subagents are unavailable or restricted, continue in single-agent mode and state that parallel delegation could not be used.
